2026-03-12T18:02:20.7313778Z [36;1mcat >user.bazelrc <<EOF[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7314336Z [36;1m# Disable the local disk cache as we use a remote cache and don't want[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7315121Z [36;1m# two copies of every output taking up disk space. The only way to[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7315534Z [36;1m# disable the disk cache is with an empty string:[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7315909Z [36;1m# https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/5308[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7316229Z [36;1mbuild --disk_cache=[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7316454Z [36;1m[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7316713Z [36;1m# Enable remote cache for our CI but minimize downloads.[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7317240Z [36;1mbuild --remote_cache=https://storage.googleapis.com/carbon-builds-github-v${CACHE_VERSION}[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7317738Z [36;1mbuild --remote_download_outputs=minimal[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7318188Z [36;1m[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7318469Z [36;1m# We import a special key into every action in order to key the Bazel[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7318920Z [36;1m# remote cache in a way that avoids collisions between different[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7319379Z [36;1m# runners. Anything that might change the system external to Bazel but[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7319841Z [36;1m# not be fully captured by the sand-boxing of the build should be used[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7320276Z [36;1m# as part of the key. We don't need to use the CPU target for example,[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7320698Z [36;1m# as that is captured by Bazel's configuration of each action. And the[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7321147Z [36;1m# Clang version is incorporated by our Clang toolchain setup. But we[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7321595Z [36;1m# do need to capture any differences between GitHub runner OSes that[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7322028Z [36;1m# don't impact the Bazel configuration to avoid collisions between[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7322372Z [36;1m# those.[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7322682Z [36;1mbuild --action_env=BAZEL_REMOTE_CACHE_KEY=github-action-ubuntu-22.04[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7323042Z [36;1m[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7323255Z [36;1mbuild --remote_upload_local_results=false[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7323528Z [36;1m[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7323811Z [36;1m# Set an artificially high jobs count. This flag controls the number[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7324278Z [36;1m# of concurrency Bazel itself uses, which is essential for actions[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7324973Z [36;1m# that are internally blocked on for example downloading results form[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7325437Z [36;1m# the cache above. Without setting this high, Bazel will pick a small[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7325881Z [36;1m# number based on the available host CPUs and the reality will be a[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7326321Z [36;1m# long chain of largely serialized download events with little or no[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7326746Z [36;1m# usage of the host machine. Fortunately, local actions are[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7327165Z [36;1m# *separately* gated on '--local_*_resources' that will avoid a large[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7327601Z [36;1m# jobs value overwhelming the host. There is a bug to make downloads[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7328062Z [36;1m# behave completely asynchronously and remove the need for this filed[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7328456Z [36;1m# back in 2018 but work seemed to not finish:[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7328796Z [36;1m# https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/6394[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7329083Z [36;1m#[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7329357Z [36;1m# There is a new effort (yay!) but until then it seems worth using the[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7329797Z [36;1m# workaround of a high jobs value. The biggest downside (increased[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7330233Z [36;1m# heap usage) seems like it isn't currently a big loss for our builds.[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7330563Z [36;1m#[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7330838Z [36;1m# Higher values like 50 have led to CI failures with network errors[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7331186Z [36;1m# and IOExceptions, see[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7331590Z [36;1m# https://discord.com/channels/655572317891461132/707150492370862090/1151605725576056934[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7332175Z [36;1mbuild --jobs=32[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7332384Z [36;1m[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7332617Z [36;1m# Avoid any cache impact from build stamping in CI.[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7332919Z [36;1mbuild --nostamp[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7333115Z [36;1m[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7333295Z [36;1m# General build options.[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7333537Z [36;1mbuild --verbose_failures[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7333777Z [36;1mtest --test_output=errors[0m
2026-03-12T18:02:20.7334010Z [36;1mEOF[0m
