2026-03-12T18:03:53.2770038Z [36;1m# GitHub sometimes has a high failure rate for Bazel's downloads (even[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2770508Z [36;1m# from GitHub URLs). Bazel exits with `1` on HTTP errors, which is hard[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2770912Z [36;1m# to distinguish from a normal, permanent error.[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2771211Z [36;1m#[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2771509Z [36;1m# This workaround runs fast commands that should always pass (although[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2771982Z [36;1m# they may be broken by an invalid PR). All errors are retried. The hope[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2772441Z [36;1m# is that this caches necessary downloads, allowing later commands to[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2773058Z [36;1m# more reliably succeed without retrying "permanent" errors.[0m
2026-03-12T18:03:53.2773383Z [36;1m#[0m
